  "local_port": 49618,
  "remote_port": 443,
  "prompt": "A bag contains 5 white, 7 red and 8 black balls. If four balls are drawn one by one without replacement, what is the probability of getting all white balls?",
  "response": "To determine the probability of drawing all white balls from the bag, we'll follow these steps:\n\n1. **Total Number of Balls:**\n   \n   - White balls: 5\n   - Red balls: 7\n   - Black balls: 8\n   \n   **Total balls = 5 (white) + 7 (red) + 8 (black) = 20 balls**\n\n2. **Total Ways to Draw 4 Balls Without Replacement:**\n   \n   The number of ways to draw 4 balls from 20 is given by the combination formula:\n   \n   \\[\n   \\text{Total ways} = \\binom{20}{4} = \\frac{20!}{4!(20-4)!} = \\frac{20 \\times 19 \\times 18 \\times 17}{4 \\times 3 \\times 2 \\times 1} = 4845\n   \\]\n\n3. **Favorable Ways to Draw 4 White Balls:**\n   \n   There are 5 white balls, and we want to draw 4 of them:\n   \n   \\[\n   \\text{Favorable ways} = \\binom{5}{4} = \\frac{5!}{4!(5-4)!} = \\frac{5 \\times 4 \\times 3 \\times 2}{4 \\times 3 \\times 2 \\times 1} = 5\n   \\]\n\n4. **Calculation of Probability:**\n   \n   The probability \\( P \\) of drawing all white balls is the ratio of favorable ways to total ways:\n   \n   \\[\n   P = \\frac{\\text{Favorable ways}}{\\text{Total ways}} = \\frac{5}{4845}\n   \\]\n   \n   Simplifying the fraction by dividing numerator and denominator by 5:\n   \n   \\[\n   P = \\frac{1}{969}\n   \\]\n\nHowever, let's verify the calculation using an alternative approach (sequential probability) to ensure accuracy.\n\n**Alternative Method (Sequential Probability):**\n\n1. **Probability of Drawing the First White Ball:**\n   \n   \\[\n   P_1 = \\frac{5}{20} = \\frac{1}{4}\n   \\]\n\n2. **Probability of Drawing the Second White Ball (without replacement):**\n   \n   \\[\n   P_2 = \\frac{4}{19}\n   \\]\n\n3. **Probability of Drawing the Third White Ball:**\n   \n   \\[\n   P_3 = \\frac{3}{18} = \\frac{1}{6}\n   \\]\n\n4. **Probability of Drawing the Fourth White Ball:**\n   \n   \\[\n   P_4 = \\frac{2}{17}\n   \\]\n\n5. **Total Probability:**\n   \n   Multiply the probabilities of each step:\n   \n   \\[\n   P = P_1 \\times P_2 \\times P_3 \\times P_4 = \\frac{1}{4} \\times \\frac{4}{19} \\times \\frac{1}{6} \\times \\frac{2}{17}\n   \\]\n   \n   Simplifying:\n   \n   \\[\n   P = \\frac{1 \\times 4 \\times 1 \\times 2}{4 \\times 19 \\times 6 \\times 17} = \\frac{8}{7752}\n   \\]\n   \n   Further simplification by dividing numerator and denominator by 8:\n   \n   \\[\n   P = \\frac{1}{969}\n   \\]\n\nBoth methods yield the same result.\n\n**Final Answer:**\n\n\\[\n\\boxed{\\dfrac{1}{969}}\n\\]",
  "temperature": 1.0,
